## ErrorModal

**Location:** `src/components/modal/ErrorModal/`

**Purpose:** Displays API error messages to users with dismiss functionality.

**Usage:**

```tsx
import { errorModalService } from 'Services/errorModalService';

// Show error
errorModalService.show({
  title: 'Error',
  message: 'Something went wrong',
});

// Or use component directly
import { ErrorModal } from 'Components/modal/ErrorModal';

<ErrorModal
  title="Error"
  message="Failed to load"
  onClose={handleClose}
/>;
```

**Props:** See `PropsT` in component file

- title: string – Error title
- message: string – Error description
- onClose: () => void – Close handler

**Features:**

- Keyboard accessible (Escape to close)
- Focus trap inside modal
- Screen reader support

**Dependencies:**

- Uses: Components/modal/Modal (base)
- Uses: Services/errorModalService

**Tests:**

- Unit: ErrorModal.test.tsx
- E2E: tests/error-modal.spec.ts
````

## Service Documentation Format

````markdown
## errorModalService

**Location:** `src/services/errorModalService.ts`

**Purpose:** Manages error modal display globally.

**Methods:**

```typescript
show(error: ApiErrorT): void    // Display error modal
hide(): void                     // Close error modal
```

**Usage:**

```typescript
import { errorModalService } from 'Services/errorModalService';

try {
  await api.fetchData();
} catch (error) {
  errorModalService.show({
    title: 'Error',
    message: error.message,
  });
}
```

**Integration:**

- Automatically triggered by axios interceptor on 4xx/5xx
- Can be called manually for custom error handling

**Dependencies:**

- Uses: Components/modal/ErrorModal
````

